      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(doctor): report official managed plugin version drift",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- **Problem**: `openclaw gateway status --deep` reports plugin version drift but `openclaw doctor` only shows plugin counts. Operators relying on doctor miss stale runtime-critical plugins. Issue #90891.\n- **Root Cause**: `noteWorkspaceStatus()` shows plugin counts but never calls `detectPluginVersionDrift()`.\n- **Fix**: Call `detectPluginVersionDrift()` after plugin counts. Best-effort (try/catch). Uses daemon-aware env and gateway version fallback like gateway status --deep.\n- **What changed**: `doctor-workspace-status.ts` (+34/-1), `doctor-health-contributions.ts` (+4/-1), `doctor-workspace-status.test.ts` (+91/-1).\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: `openclaw doctor` showed only plugin counts with no drift warning. After fix, official managed plugins with mismatched versions trigger a warning with the repair command.\n- **Real environment tested**: Windows 11 x64 (10.0.22631), Node 24.16.0, OpenClaw 2026.6.2. `openclaw doctor --non-interactive` run from source checkout verifies no regression (all plugins aligned).\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**: `corepack pnpm openclaw doctor --non-interactive`\n- **Evidence after fix**:\n\nHealthy run (no drift — correct, all plugins match gateway version):\n```\n◇  Plugins ──────╮\n│                │\n│  Loaded: 72    │\n│  Imported: 0   │\n│  Disabled: 60  │\n│  Errors: 0     │\n│                │\n├────────────────╯\n```\n\nPositive drift path verified via real `detectPluginVersionDrift` call with the reporter's exact scenario (codex on 2026.5.30-beta.1, gateway on 2026.6.2):\n```\n=== Reporter scenario: codex on 2026.5.30-beta.1, gateway on 2026.6.2 ===\n\nPlugin version drift DETECTED:\n  - codex: 2026.5.30-beta.1 -> expected 2026.6.2\n\nFix: openclaw plugins update codex && openclaw gateway restart\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix**: No false warning in healthy state. When drift exists, the same `detectPluginVersionDrift` function used by `gateway status --deep` correctly identifies stale official plugins and formats the repair command.\n- **What was not tested**: A live environment with actual old managed plugin installs and a running gateway. The drift detector itself is unchanged from `gateway status --deep` which the reporter already validated with real output. Unit tests cover both the positive drift display and the best-effort error path.\n\nFixes #90891\n",
        "branch": "fix/doctor-plugin-version-drift-90891",
